      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hey there, I'd be happy to help you craft that email! It's a delicate balance, but I can certainly help you make it sound professional, empathetic, and human. Just a quick thought: while you're drafting this, you might want to consider if there's a specific reason you chose the other candidate, or if you simply wanted to give the final candidate a chance to learn from the process. That could add a nice layer of transparency.\n\nHere's a draft you can use:\n\n---\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for [Job Title]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us and for your enthusiasm about the [Job Title] role. We truly appreciated the opportunity to get to know you and your experience.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we've decided to move forward with another candidate who has a particularly strong alignment with our current project goals. While we were impressed by your skills and the great conversations we had, we believe this role is best suited for someone with a slightly different background.\n\nWe want to be transparent that this decision is not a reflection of your abilities or potential. In fact, we were genuinely impressed by your performance in the final round.",
