      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a great addition! Adding context about the high volume of applicants and a hopeful note about future opportunities will really soften the blow and show you value them as a person, not just a resume. Here is the revised version with those elements woven in naturally:\n\n---\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for [Job Title]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us and for your enthusiasm about the [Job Title] role. We truly appreciated the opportunity to get to know you and your experience.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we've decided to move forward with another candidate who has a particularly strong alignment with our current project goals. While we were impressed by your skills and the great conversations we had, we believe this role is best suited for someone with a slightly different background.\n\nWe want to be transparent that this decision is not a reflection of your abilities or potential. In fact, we were genuinely impressed by your performance in the final round. Given the incredibly competitive nature of our hiring process this cycle—with a massive pool of applicants—we simply couldn't pass up the chance to bring someone else on board.\n\nThat said, we will absolutely keep your resume in mind for future roles where your",
